A survey of passengers showed that more than 20 percent of them knowingly or unknowingly carried prohibited items through the U.S. Transportation Security Administration checkpoints on board the plane. At least six percent of passengers boarded the plane with a knife or other sharp object.
Less than one percent of passengers say they have been delayed in finding out they have traveled with a firearm, ammunition, or explosive device.
