A British court on Thursday sentenced four members of an Islamist cell known as the Three Musketeers to life in prison for plotting a terrorist attack against police and the military, prosecutors said.
Four men, two of whom attended a training camp in Pakistan and had previously been convicted of similar crimes, were arrested last August.
