China has a lack of tourists.
Beijing is losing billions because of its visa policy.
For decades, China has been trying to exert its influence without the use of force.
It spends $10 billion annually to support language schools and build universities abroad, pushing its entertainment industry to foreign markets, and trying to attract Western tourists.
Beijing is not doing that.
The state media are talking about a plan to turn tourism into a driving force for economic transformation and modernization.
However, the number of arrivals rose by only 3.8 percent last year, and roughly 80 percent of tourists to China came from Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan.
