The series “Summer to Survive” and “Comrade Detective” play on a nostalgic string
This iteration of the story is nostalgic for both the characters of the famous 1980s; for the dirty 1990s (when geniuses David Wain and Michael Showalter introduced the comedy sketch "The State" on MTV); and, of course, for modern times, namely 2001, before stars such as Elizabeth Banks, Amy Poehler and Paul Rudd fled to larger projects.
As a cultural artifact, it is a light parody and at the same time an embodiment of our modern Facebook era of lasting memories.
From the French point of view, it looks like someone is running out of breath.
The series “First Day of Camp” worked surprisingly well - not only thanks to absurd humor (an example can be the story of the creation of a talking can of vegetables, which was narrated by H. Jon Benjamin).
The authors turned away from the main funny point - middle-aged actors who play teenage horny children - and could not make fun of previous events.
