One-room apartment with a complicated layout - to get to the bedroom, you had to go through the kitchen - Joanne wanted to add storage space and a mezzanine to take advantage of the high ceiling.
“I wanted a high ceiling, big windows and lots of light.
Those were my demands,” she said.
To this end, she employed Erfan Azadi from Duck & Shed's design and design studio based in Notting Hill and used a nearly four-foot ceiling to create a home that was not just a project but also a place to live.
