Two distinguished journalists talk about what would be safer: taking their children to an office that was bombed in 2009 or leaving them at home.
Security experts wrote three simple words on the blackboard: adversaries, neutrals, and allies.
They ask journalists to give names to every word - no evidence is needed, just use imagination and foreboding.
To choose from - drug dealers, politicians, traders and journalists are suspected of taking money from the government or drug cartels - a catalogue of criminals whose job it is to cover up criminal acts.
