The director of the newspaper, Bojorquez, is on a day trip to Washington to seek international support and justice for Valdez's death.
In a meeting with Governor Sinaloa the day after Valdez's murder, Ramirez accused the authorities of spying on journalists and murdering them for proclaiming the truth.
Meanwhile, she asked to be transferred to another department out of fear that her anger might compromise her impartiality.
